==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Traversing
<hw>Trav"ers*ing</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Adjustable laterally; having a
lateral motion, or a swinging motion; adapted for giving lateral
motion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Traversing plate</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>one of
two thick iron plates at the hinder part of a gun carriage, where the
handspike is applied in traversing the piece.</cd> <au>Wilhelm.</au> --
<col><b>Traversing platform</b></col> <fld>(Mil.)</fld>, <cd>a platform
for traversing guns.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Travertine</ent>⟦br⟧
